						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying under the tamarind tree near the Vishṇu temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Sadāśivarāya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1465, Krōdhi, Kārttīka, śu. 12.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to register some gift to the god (name lost) made by Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara China-Timmayadēva-Mahārāja of Ātrēya-gōtra.</p>						

						</summary>
